4. Specific Requirements
4.1 Functional Requirements
1. Network Modeling & Configuration
The system shall:

Allow registration of devices

Allow assignment of devices to LEAs

Allow creation of logical links between devices

Allow assignment of responsible officers

Allow tagging devices with priority levels

2. Fault Management
The system shall:

Simulate AC, BL, Node Down, and Link Down alarms

Detect missing heartbeats

Mark devices as DOWN when failure occurs

Store alarm history

Clear alarms when restored

3. Impact Analysis
The system shall:

Identify root cause using deterministic rules

Determine upstream vs local failure

Traverse downstream graph

Mark devices as IMPACTED

Group impacted devices by priority level

4. Network Visualization
The system shall:

Display device status in real time

Show root cause information

Provide map-based visualization

Show topology relationships

5. Notification Management
The system shall:

Generate real-time notifications for failures

Store notifications in database

Allow users to mark notifications as read

6. Logging & Audit
The system shall:

Record system events

Record alarm history

Provide read-only log view

Maintain timestamped audit trail

